<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's an exploit involving items that are usually no drop but because Verant forgot about FV ruleset they aren't no drop here.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This reminds me of how the Mark of Execution was once no drop. A certain guild did the trial once, and pass around the mark so other could complete the quest thus by-passing the hardest part. I then found it odd how a few days later this Mark of Execution became no drop. Perhaps someone from this guild decided to petition it after they had already taken advantage of the exploit and keyed all their members.<br>
<br>
Without the flag from the quest involving the Mark of Execution, you cannot gain entrance to the Plane of Valor, and thus not gain entrance to Halls of Honor by killing Aerin`Dar. If I were to guess, I'd say maybe half the members of said guild have the Mark of Execution thus making them even eligible to be in Halls of Honor.<br>
<br>
One more thing. Rollen you speak of pride and how we've lessened your achievements, I don't see how you can call yourself prideworthy when you had to ask for the assistance of Dreadstorm to help you kill Aerin`Dar. When Resolution can take him by themselves, then that perhaps would be prideworthy, but until you do I see no reason to be flaming anyone. This is not a slight against Dreadstorm, for you know I have the utmost respect for you.<br>
<br>
Do we plan on killing Aerin`Dar? Of course, it would be silly not to. Killing Aerin`Dar is a great accomplishment, one that I will not deny my members from having.<br>
<br>
With the changing of leadership of both Resolution and Fire and Fury, I was hoping for a better relationship between the two guilds. Unfortunately, Rollen is to caught up in what we are doing to realize the great achievements that he and his guild has accomplished. But if Rollen believes this is the best way to handle a situation, I guess I will be reconsidering my future actions as well.<br>
<br>
I am not one to speak out. I prefer to sit back, listen and watch. This will most likely be the only time I comment on this here. Anything else can be taken up in game.<br>
